PM Harold Wilson was forced to go to the polls early after his parliamentary majority was slashed to one in a series of by-election losses. But his gamble paid off and Labour won a resounding victory with a 96-seat majority.  39 years ago (1983) Tens of thousands of peace protestors formed a 14-mile human chain in Berkshire to protest against the presence of American missiles on British soil. The actress Julie Christie joined the CND demonstration, which stretched from the RAF base at Greenham Common to past the Aldermaston nuclear research centre. 22 years ago (2000) An enigma machine used by the Germans to encrypt messages in the Second World War was stolen from Bletchley Park Museum, Buckinghamshire. It was later returned in a package to broadcaster Jeremy Paxman. The identity of the thief remains unknown. 